====Verb====
{{en-verb|spells|spelling|'''[[spelled]] '''or''' [[spelt]]'''}}

# to comprise a word
#: ''The letters “a”, “n” and “d” '''spell''' “and”.''
# {{context|sometimes with “out”}} to write or say the letters that form a word or part of a word.
# {{transitive|figurative}} to [[indicate]] that (some event) will occur
#: ''This '''spells''' trouble.''
# {{transitive|figurative|with “out”}} to [[clarify]]
#* '''2003''', U.S. Senator Ben Nighthorse Campbel, ''Hearing before the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation'', ISBN 1422334120:
#*: When we get elected, for instance, we get one of these, and we are pretty much told what is in it, and it is our responsibility to read it and understand it, and if we do no, the Ethics Committee, we can call them any time of day and ask them to '''spell''' it out for us[...].
# {{transitive}} to work in place of (someone).

